one cell phone picture. just a green dot on the picture, not what we saw completely

content.detailedDescription: While retrieving an item from my car i looked up into the sky and saw a very bright light or series of lights in the sky traveling north to south over my home. i called out to my nephew to come look at it. we then heard a plane and my nephew said it sounds like  plane. immediately a very obvious airplane passed over the house from east to west at a lowe altitude than the unidentifiable craft. we continued to watch the lights until they disappeared from view. very strange. we were both concerned at the size of the lights and the speed. we researched the possibility of another type of craft being present but could find no information and decided to make the report here
content.summary: Extreme bright craft flying north to south quickly no flashing lights no sound obvious airplane travelled east to west at same time but had sound and flashing lights

content.detailedDescription:
While working off 34 mile and fisher road, i noticed a bright white/red light up in the sky just over 3 miles away, but was about the size of a pea from where i saw it. i called to a co-worker to come and take a look at it so i wasnt the only one to see it. after he saw it and we asked each other what it was, he went back inside. i stayed out to observe it for about another minute before it just vanished. it did not move from what i could see, it just disappeared.  the light did not get brighter, or change position from its spot it was hovering. it was brighter then any airplane lights i have ever seen. the main colors i could see were red and white. white being the brightest with the red flashing/pulsing at the same time. 

when i first say the light i thought it was a helicopter, but it was brighter then that and not moving.

i have a feeling of unknowing. i have been living/working in this area my whole life and have never seen anything like this before.
content.summary: Flashing light with red and white hovering to the southwest fo romeo mi

content.detailedDescription:
We were out on the pool deck enjoying the evening when i noticed something up in the night sky that struck me as unusual.
 
it was very bright and color changing rapidly through most of the rainbow spectrum.

obviously not a plane, i went quickly and brought out my 5" reflector telescope and called my wife and 4 kids out to witness the event.

we all had time to look at the object in the night sky with the telescope and we then decided to try and capture video of the object with a i-phone camera through the telescope and this with good results per the video posted.

shape of the object is quite saucer like typical of many observations by others.

kids called over their friends for a look at it through the telescope, 9 total witnesses on the event.
content.summary: Very colorful long duration sighting with video captured through 5" telescope

content.detailedDescription: Was on my balcony with a friend, we saw an ufo that was traveling east from our perspective, we were facing south.  it would light every 45s approximately very verrrry brightly, then completely go black as if it were spinning and one part of it was reflecting back to us only.  it flew right past the moon i believe above.  i think it was traveling in a straight line but was not the easiest to track as you could only see it when it lit up.  i have basically ruled out plane, could be satellite but i assumed they don't spin? very curious what this was. actually went inside and grabbed phone camera and i believe it was able to pickup the light but it wasn't recording cause i failed to hit record button. but the video is just more evidence the description is all that matters because its easy to describe what we saw. very strange. whatever is was i assume it was spinning.  very interesting. gonna try to see it again tonight, would love to hear back.
content.summary: Lights up every ~45s very brightly

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my backyard, taking my dog out to per. i simply looked up, and was immediately awe struck by the beauty of an amazing craft simply hovering in the sky. there was no mistaking, the craft i was looking at was not of this world, and left me speechless as i gazed in awe at the brilliant gold lights it was giving off.

the object appeared wedding cake shaped, very odd, and it was covered in what looked like bulb shaped objects peppered all over the craft that were radiating the most amazing, pure gold color i have ever seen.

i screamed for my room mate to come out, when i looked back it was gone.
the sighting covered in pittsburg, california, the craft was hovering over the san pablo bay. it was at least a mile away, and even at that distance appeared extremely radiant, and the size of a shipping container. at that distance it makes it considerably larger in size.

i will never forget what i saw last night. it was a very enlightening experience, and if you'd been there too, you'd say the same two things,
1. it was not of this earth
2. the pure gold light radiating from the bulbs around the craft were absolutely mesmerizing.
content.summary: Amazing wedding cake shaped ufo with brilliant gold lights radiating from bulbs all over craft

content.detailedDescription: It was the night of the lunar eclipse in april 14-15, 2014. i had just finished playing a series of computer games with my neighbors in los angeles, ca near the lax airport on south la cienega blvd. g-pa and daniel both stepped outside of the computer room and i was admiring the lovely red moon with a new-found friend. next thing you know it, we all 3, were looking up at this red moon in awe, so we all decided to catch a photo of this lunar eclipse. i didn't know my phone was on the setting to take 2 frames instead of just one photo at a time. when i reviewed the series of photos, the 2nd  frame caught a light of some sort, but in motion or something like that. my neighbor tried to say it was a reflection or light trick but it was just too visible to be anything less than a real phenomena. i still have the pictures to this day.
content.summary: Occurred during april 14-15 2014 lunar eclipse. took a picture of red moon in 3 frames on cellphone, it appeared only on the middle frame photo.

content.detailedDescription: Walking down bridlegate lane dusk time from elvaston castle derby. i had 4 children with me aged from 6 months (in a pushchair) to 10 years. eldest child looked east? and asked "what is that?" i looked in the direction and saw (this hard to describe in words) a large triangular object that seemed to blend into the surrounding area you wouldn't of noticed it if it wasn't pointed out which is amazing as it was very big. it was a metallic grey/dark colour with lights on the underside of it.It was perfectly still with no sound at all. it was just above the tree line which would of placed it in the shardlow road area alvaston derby. the atmosphere was i can only describe as eerielie quiet with no one but us on the lane. i don't know why but all i thought was get the kids away as fast as i could.So i down played it and said it's nothing and walked away as fast as we could. i did not look back just kept looking forward. i recently asked the eldest child if they could remember this incident and they could not in fact all the children who are now adults have no memory of it.To be honest i wish i couldn't either as i would be happy never to see anything like that again. i told my husband as soon as i got home and asked if he knew  of any plane that could stay still and make no noise he said no. this has bothered me for many years and have told no one of this but since hearing of your organization i feel i can share my experience with someone who will not think i am mad.
content.summary: Large silent triangle shape 3lights on the underside

content.detailedDescription: My grandmother first seen these lights off are back porch and called me over to look at them. they looked like lights that were dancing in the sky around each other. i have never seen anything like that before and seen nothing like it since. i remember the next day when i woke up in the morning i went down stairs to get a soda around 8am and before i new it it was around 4pm. i new that i had the same soda because i had 8 of them in the refrigerator and at 4 i still had 7 left. the soda was still cold. that night my stomach felt like i had a gut full of razor blades and vomited one time. the pains went away after that. i was around 14 when this happened and i am 40 years old now. i still am having a lot of trouble with my stomach and my doctors can't find out why. i also have some very odd dreams since then. please help my find out what's going on.
content.summary: I oberved 3 lights that appeared to be dancing around each other.

content.detailedDescription: Was at the dog park behind southold rec center in new york (long island).  it was a clear day 10/21/15 around 5pm.  noticed something in the air well above the trees but below aircraft flight path.  it was moving slowly north from the hamptons (south).  tried to get a friend to see it but he couldn't see it: "my eyes aren't good".  watched it for about 10 minutes move north, then turn east.  structure was metallic silver, reflective, with a red light (dome?) on top that would flash ocasionally, especially when turning.  what caught my eye was it was a vertical rectangle, clearly without wings.  no sound.  but it probably was several miles away from me, moving away, slowly.  looked up vertical aircraft online and nothing fit.  looked up vertical ufo and saw one pictured on youtube in mexico city dropping orbs.  that was what i saw, without the orbs.  no pictures.  sorry!  will bring cellphone in the future to dog park.
content.summary: Saw vertical rectangle with ocasional red dome light for about 10 minutes

content.detailedDescription:
it was 8:45pm, july-7-1997 white sands missile range.
     i was leaving work and heading west on nike ave.  i had just reached the horse shoe curve and noticed in the distant mountains an orange ball of light which i thought might be a fire burning two-thirds the way up the mountain side.  there were fires in that same place the year before.  the smoke of those fires invaded main post.  as i continued to drive west on nike ave., i noticed that this was not a fire but something that was fiery orange in color and was floating down the mountain.  when the object was about half way down the mountain it headed north towards main post.  i continued to drive west on nike ave., towards main post.  the object then changed from orange to a luminous white.  the object then headed in my direction and stopped half way down nike ave.  it stayed illuminated all the way from the mountain to the halfway point of nike ave.  the light intensity stayed the same too.  
     the object was about 3 to 4 car lengths away from me, about a stone throw. i pulled over onto the shoulder of the road and stopped my car.  the object started to descend and i thought it was going to land but it did not.  it came within about seven feet of the ground and stopped in the air.   i waited to see dust kick up around it but there was none.  it looked like the sphere that carried the “good witch” in the “wizard of oz” movie.  it was a perfect sphere in its shape approximately 9 to 12 feet in diameter.
     this object just stopped in the air and didn’t float around or wobble but stayed in one place.  any other aircraft would wobble a little to compensate for air currents.  there was no sound coming from this object like motors which other aircraft do produce.  and there was no wind blowing that night.
    the object was so luminous that it was like looking right into a 100 watt light bulb at night and seeing nothing but the light.  if someone was inside the object they may have been blinded.  
     i parked my car on the opposite side of the road shoulder facing in the direction of the object.  i then saw the object or light shut off.  i waited a moment and the object turned back on again.   i thought if there was any intelligence on board this thing it might understand mathematics.  so i turned my headlights off and then blinked the headlights once, twice, and three times, then twice, then once again.  this would show addition and subtraction in its simplest form.  
     now the object started to move in the direction from which it came.  it followed the same flight path back the same way it had come, as though it was following a programmed flight course.  i continued to drive west on nike ave.  keeping an eye on it until it went over the mountain, heading towards las cruces.
     this thing flew faster than i was driving which was 55 mph.   i headed home going north on owen road which leads to highway 70.  as i clover leafed around to get on highway 70, i was now facing south and looking at the mountains where the object flew over.  i could see two smaller bright lights coming over the mountain and they were together.  it looked like headlights of a car flying over the mountain heading north.  the lights flying parallel to each other split apart, one going west and the other going east and both turned back to the mountain they just come over to go back over it again.  at this time i noticed a third light, it was a red blinking light hovering beyond the back side of the mountain, not moving.  when all three lights met together they disappeared behind the mountain.  after that, i did not see anything else.  i continued to go home.
to this day i don’t know what i saw.
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Saw unknown object flying in the sky.  object came close to me, then left.
content.locationName: White Sands Missile Range, New Mexico

content.detailedDescription: We had just parked our car and we're walking through the parking lot towards the restaurant when all the power went out on the whole block. for some reason i turned around and looked up toward the sky when i saw a bright light shooting across the sky at an unusually high rate of speed. at first, i thought it was a jet of some kind, but then the object split into two smaller objects. the smaller objects continued to move across the sky in an upward direction before vanishing. i remember how eerily quite everything was. there was no engine noise as you would expect to hear from an aircraft, not even when the object split into two smaller objects, just silence. when i first noticed the object, i pointed towards it and instinctively yelled, "look!" at which time, everyone in my group and in the parking lot with us turned around and looked up at the light. my whole family witnessed this event and remembers, in detail, what they saw; what we all saw.
content.summary: The power went out on the whole block. looked up in the sky and saw a bright light shooting across the sky that split into two smaller lights then disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: Since i was 14 i have had encounters with ufo/paranormal. i also live in a house now that is visited by ghost. my daughter and myself have many experiences with this.  but ghost do not scare me like the ufo happenings do...Its almost like we can manage or protect ourselves from ghost, but with this other, you have no control..I have had bright orbs invade my house, scan my daughter and show up outside my windows and jet off so fast...From my first encounter i recall at 14, i knew there was not a lot of people to talk too about this..My most 2 recent things happened this year 2015...I seen a small craft over my house about 20 ft in the air..I studied it for the few seconds while it was there, i was not scared at all..  i looked online at so many photos of ufo until i found a pic of the one i had just seen, that type was last seen in 1952. there was no smoke, lights nothing dramatic about this craft. it was just there and then gone. somehow i felt they didn't even notice me sitting in a chair almost under them..The most troubling account happened this year. i live a rural area of oklahoma..I had been taking care of dogs left at a house,up the road from my house. i was feeding them everyday after work..Weather was cold, i bought blankets and put in the dog houses..I felt someone had been helping my with keeping the blankets in the dog house and such, i looked across the street and seen a house, i just thought someone bought the property and moved in with a prefab/mobile home. i thought maybe these people are helping which will be great!! i was going to ask them and introduce myself,but didn't look like anyone was home, so i didn't go, the next day or two, i see the house again, looks like they are all at work so i'd go another time and ask if they have been helping with the dogs. about the 4th time, i seen they were home, lights on, trucks in the driveway..So i decide to go to ask them about the dogs,but i can not find their driveway entrance, i go the  next guys property over and ask, how do i get into their driveway,(the new people) he didn't know anything about it..I went on home..Im telling my boyfriend in text at least 3 times on different days, that i think the people that live across the road are helping, finally he asked...'what house are you talking about? and i said, the new one right across the road, its white with black shutters and they drive a white pickup..He did not recall seeing a new house there, over the weekend..I kept saying well its there now, no big deal...Well when he came for the next weekend, we went up to feed the dogs and he said, 'wheres the house you kept texting about?' when i looked up to point it out, it wasn't there..I even had him walk up the hill and check..I seen this house on several different occasions, before work, after work..I know what i saw, i can describe it in detail..But its not there now..I was so shaken up and bothered by this. i drove to the neighbors house with my boyfriend to ask him, if i had came there last week to ask him about how to get into the driveway of the new house, he said yes, you came here and asked..Ghost, orbs, ufo's have not shaken me up as bad as that event this year..I am a 55 yr old female, i do not drink, no drugs.I was witnessing something in a different reality, several times that is not showing up now..I started to cry and get very upset when he said, there is no house there..And yet i know all the details of that house, porch lighting, wooded stairs and could see people moving inside like getting ready to settle down for night after a day at work..
content.summary: Seen a small craft hovering about 20 ft above my house, i have more important encounters then this last one

content.detailedDescription:
Got out of bed to go to the bathroom.  noticed a very bright light in the sky.  as i stared at it, i noticed it was dancing/pulsating/changing shape/had pieces break off and reabsorb.  at times different colors would emit from it.  it stayed in the same general location - about 35-40 degrees off the ground looking due east.  with the known meteor shower, i assumed this was part of it, but today realized that meteors probably don't stand still and behave like that. 

i woke up everyone in the house so the four of us witnessed it. we went outside and watched for almost 15 minutes.  again, it stayed in generally the same spot, but would dance, bounce, emit color, smaller pieces would break off (at one point forming a straight line), then get reabsorbed.  it dimmed/disappeared and we went back to bed, but from bed, i saw it light up again.  

no clue what this was.  meteor activity?  ufo?
content.summary: Bright light shone through window at 2am. danced. flickered. smaller pieces broke off then reabsorbed.

content.detailedDescription:
Stepped in to the backyard to let the dogs out prior to bed.  was looking up at the moon and noticed a bright pulse of white light to the west of the moon.  first impression was a possible small meteor or iridium flare from a satellite.  about 10-15 seconds later, the flash occurred again slightly more east of the first.  continuing to watch, the flash occurred every 10-15 seconds with the movement from west to east for the first 2 minutes or so and was not consistent between each sighting.  further observation showed the light pulse change from an east to a more southern path.  while watching, a passenger airline passed from west to east directly in the path of the object which was much higher as observed as the pulse of light occurred during the transit of the airliner.

area is near a lot of small airports, hartsfield jackson/atl international airport to my south, and dobbins afb (and lockheed martin) a few miles down the road.  air traffic earlier in the evening was heavy.  

this light pulse was viewed looking towards the city with several light sources from nearby houses, thus the attempt at recording the object using an iphone 5s was unsuccessful and did not have my usual nikon camera available.  video was attempted 2-3 minutes after first noticing the object and total recording of the video was over 4 minutes before the object moved too far south for me to view over houses and trees.  total viewing was 9-10 minutes and object did change directions from its original eastern path within the first few minutes of observation once it moved from the west of the moon to the east side.

no stranger to sky gazing and familiar with passenger and military configurations of light pulses along with frequent satellite viewing and iridium flares.  this pulse was unusual and time between pulses does not fit airline strobes and landing lights.  object was also too high for conventional aircraft based on other air traffic in different altitudes also visible.

light:  bright white flash/pulse, longer duration than typical aircraft pulses and duration between flashes was between 10-15 seconds.  time between each pulse was not always the same.
size:  size of light as seen during each pulse was 3/4 that of venus seen early morning.
height:  unknown, but beyond conventional aircraft
speed:  slow moving, distance traveled between each pulse was 3-5 degrees
viewing angle:  looking ssw at moon roughly 25 degrees for first few minutes and 60 degrees at final sighting due south of position
content.summary: Bright flash/pulse 10-15 seconds apart

content.detailedDescription:
1995 september. i was working at a farm near tenbury wells in worcestershire. an old boy there told me of a ufo sighting the previous year. it was late at night and he was sub soiling a field. an glowing orb appeared at speed and stopped about 20ft above the tractor. he estimated it to be about 3ft in diameter. it hovered above him for several seconds before flying off at speed the way it had come. 

i took this as a joke to wind me up as i was working till 3-4 in the mornings, ploughing. a few days later i was doing just that when, at about 1am, i saw some lights dashing around the sky to the north. my immediate thoughts where of the plough lights reflecting around the cab, as it was very similar. there was mass' of muck flies flying around these lamps leaving little light trails behind them. the light in the shy gave a similar appearance. i stopped and turned all the lights out. they where still there. then i looked behind me to see if it was a house light, but there was just darkness. now i was getting curious. i opened the sunroof and stuck my head out for a good uninterrupted line of sight. this was no reflection. the main light (holding your arm out straight with a uk penny to give you a size comparison) was surrounded by a mass of much smaller lights that circled in a flitting motion around its girth. every now and then one of them would disappear into the distance and return from that direction 15 seconds or so later. i watched for about ten minutes in which time the smaller light went off many times. all at once the small lights merged with the larger orb, and a few seconds later went vertically at huge speed. it was like watching a star trek space ship going to warp speed from stand still. it was truly amazing.

the following morning i told a colleague about it. he suggested quizzing the old boy in more detail. a few minutes later he pulled into the yard. we went straight up to him and asked him to tell us again what he had seen, which he did. i then asked him if there had been anything else in the sky. "yes, there was". this was like getting blood from a stone. we did not want to put words or ideas into his head so asked if it was an aircraft. "no it was the mother ship and all the other little lights." he then described the mother ship in much greater detail. he said it was way bigger than the moon and guessed it to be more than 100 yards in diameter with 20 - 30 smaller lights buzzing backwards and forwards. 

there was a series on the tv. seaquest dsv. on this series they had small orbs, with sensors, around the sub which they called "whiskers". that is what i would call the smaller lights. they gave the impression that they were gathering readings and information. the old boy had seen this at much closer distance and, where i didn't feel threatened, he was terrified. he still did night shifts but always had the tractor doors locked.
content.summary: Large orbe surrounded by much smaller orbes. these would flit around, occasionally disapearing and returning a few moments later. departed vertically at warp speed.

content.detailedDescription: I was letting my dog out on his chain about 9 p.M. out back of my apartments and was standing out there as we had recently had coyote attacks in the area. i looked to the left and three orbs about 500 feet up. cant tell if there were three objects flying in a staggered formation or one object with the center light offset, but the lights stayed the same distance apart from each other and flew a steady path from north to south not blinking one time like nothing i've seen before. a plane was flying about half a mile above it from east to west with obvious red and blue blinking lights.I watched this for about 45 seconds to a minute until it went out of view over a tree line. when i first seen it i was excited i suppose, i first started thinking though that maybe it was military, but the more i thought about it i wasnt so sure. i came back inside and told my wife. the next day some friends suggested could they have been chinese lanterns. i instantly say no cause they would have changed spacing and flickered.
content.summary: Appeared to be three orbs but could not tell if it was one craft or three

content.detailedDescription: As i was driving home from my girlfriends house in the morning, i noticed a dull orange fireball/orb slowly moving just above the tree line. at first i thought it was a plane or maybe a chinese lantern, but those thoughts quickly faded as i watched the object change from orb like to a elongated cigar shape with a pulsating tail. i was so shocked by what i was seeing i didnt realize i had come to a complete stop in the middle of the road. so i pulled over and continued observing the object. to my amazment that pulsating "tail" i mentioned, broke off of the main object and hovered and pulsated before following the main object and then disappeared.  i continued to watch and the  again main object broke of another piece that pulsated and followed the main object for a little before blinking out. then the main object accelerated quickly to the upper atmosphere until i could no longer see it.
content.summary: Ufo sighting in early morning hours

content.detailedDescription: My back porch faces the west towards the mountains. i can see alot of the sky facing west. about 3 wks ago i was smoking on the back porch and noticed a really bright star. as i was watching it,it moved to the n.About 3 inches.  as i continued watching it moved straight down about 4 inches  continued to stop and go in various directions- up, down,north,south and diagonal. it will be still for 10-15 seconds and then move usually very fast. sometimes slow. i have seen it every night over arvada,broomfield and westminster,all nieghboring cities.I can go back out an hr later and it will be there in basically the same area of the sky. but everynight i see it over 1 of these 3 cities.Tonight it had been rainy all day and cloudy so i didnt think i would see it,but i did-2 of them! it was so cloudy i couldnt see any stars but i could see the same light zipping all over the sky. it was harder to see tonight because of the clouds,but it was there. i saw 2 of them tonight being very active, moving 6 to 7 inches at a time- all different directions. it is not a star or a plane or a helicopter or a shooting star. i am not an idiot!!! my daughter and her friend have seen it too and they report seeing some lights changing from green. yellow and blue. on clear nights i can see illuminating light lighting up the sky around it. i watch it everynight and want to know what it is and aren't other people seeing this too? i could watch it for hrs but my neck gets sore lol. i don't have a good camera so i have not been able to tape it, but i will be watching everynight.

content.detailedDescription: I could not sleep one morning. so i sat on couch and looked out window, the out of nowhere a huge silver circle appeared, thought it was a planet until it became  hudge. then  it disappeared before i knew it i was face to face with a hudge brown or gold color honey combed oval object right outside my window. just siting there face to face at my window less than a foot or two away right outside.. i had both window blinds up and thought it was reflection so i turned around and looked there was nothing to reflect. just this hudge honey combed object face to face with me, for about 5 minutes . there was a tree right behind it, then i observed the same oval shaped honeycombed object move immediately right over my home up higher in  the sky and  faced some kind of ship or craft with yellow lights. the feelings i felt , i was not afraid, more liked surprised, and awed, wanted to go outside and touch it thats how close it was. about a few days later, i was coming from my brothers house, and was heading to mine when as i was walking a cross the yard and noticed a similar ship or craft that the oval honey combed object faced, right over my nighbors yard. i could not make out object cause it was dark all i saw was strange yellow lights , and they  were not street lights cause they were to high in the sky.
